ge in the commensurate propagation vector and\ndevelopment of a ferromagnetic component at $H=3$\\,kOe, followed by a series of\ntransitions before the fully field-induced ferromagnetic phase is reached at $H\n= 7$\\,kOe. This explains the nature of the steps previously reported in\nfield-dependent magnetization measurements. A very similar behaviour is also\nobserved for the $H\\parallel$ [0 1 1] crystal direction.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 26 Feb 2022 17:27:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-04-06"}
