{"id":"2202.13367","submitter":"Haoyue Tang","authors":"Haoyue Tang, Yuchao Chen, Jintao Wang, Pengkun Yang, Leandros\n  Tassiulas","title":"Age Optimal Sampling Under Unknown Delay Statistics","comments":"Accepted and to appear, IEEE Transactions on Information Theory","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1109/TIT.2022.3233782","report-no":null,"categories":"cs.IT math.IT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  This paper revisits the problem of sampling and transmitting status updates\nthrough a channel with random delay under a sampling frequency constraint\n\\cite{sun_17_tit}. We use the Age of Information (AoI) to characterize the\nstatus information freshness at the receiver. The goal is to design a sampling\npolicy that can minimize the average AoI when the statistics of delay is\nunknown. We reformulate the problem as the optimization of a renewal-reward\nprocess, and propose an online sampling strategy based on the Robbins-Monro\nalgorithm. We prove that the proposed algorithm satisfies the sampling\nfrequency constraint. Moreover, when the transmission delay is bounded and its\ndistribution is absolutely continuous, the average AoI obtained by the proposed\nalgorithm converges to the minimum AoI when the number of samples $K$ goes to\ninfinity with probability 1. We show that the optimality gap decays with rate\n$\\mathcal{O}\\left(\\ln K/K\\right)$, and the proposed algorithm is minimax rate\noptimal. Simulation results validate the performance of our proposed algorithm.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 27 Feb 2022 13:59:40 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 1 Apr 2022 13:19:04 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 20 Apr 2022 15:22:59 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 13 Jun 2022 22:08:49 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Tue, 3 Jan 2023 22:09:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-05"}
