q$7000 au.\nRadiative transfer effects within the pre-stellar core cause the\nNH$_2$D(1$_{11}$-1$_{01}$) emission to appear centrally concentrated, with a\nflattened distribution within the central $\\simeq$3000 au, unlike the 1.3 mm\ndust continuum emission which shows a clear peak within the central\n$\\simeq$1800 au. This prevented NH$_2$D freeze-out to be detected in previous\nobservations, where the central 1000 au cannot be spatially resolved.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 27 Feb 2022 14:37:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-04-20"}
